    <text id="A1422T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Carroll thanks his correspondent for sending him clothing, asks her to send some
                    under garments and discusses the whereabouts of people she might know.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-09-22"><abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 22 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">Camp Chase Ohio</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><del hand="h1">Mrs</del> Mrs Virginia Miller</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>a few lines to let you that I hasten To drop you myself and W E. Millers Received
                    The clothing you sent to him and myself and and feel Ourselves under many
                    obligations to you for them we <abbr expan="received">Rec</abbr> the following
                    Articles Viz 2 coats 2 pairs pants 3 pairs shoes 2 Vests 1 Hat of <orig
                        reg="which">whitch</orig> we stood <orig reg="very">Verry</orig>
                    <orig reg="much">mutch</orig> in need of as The cold Weather is approaching I
                    have written Several letters By Flag Truce But have not gotten no answer yet
                    your letter was <orig reg="received">Rec</orig> also <del hand="h1">y</del> you
                    came I wish you would send me Some under clothing as I am Entirely Destitute of
                    a change of clothing of that kind I almost Hate to ask you But I have no
                    Relations living North Nor nobody's address But you and as soon as time will
                    admit I will Repay you for what Expense you have already gone To I will close
                    Hoping to hear from you soon</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Friend</salute>
                    <signed>Franklin Carroll</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">PS Carlile Rystoe who lived with your Brothers <unclear>
                            <orig reg="son">so</orig>
                        </unclear> Tomy in <orig reg="Middlebrook">middlebrook</orig> was killed in
                            <orig reg="August">august</orig> 62 John R <orig reg="Berry's"
                        >Berrys</orig> Son James was killed June 62 I stated about <abbr
                            expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> W S H Baylor was killed at The 2 Battle of
                        Manassas But was A <abbr expan="Brigadier">Brig</abbr> General in place of
                            <abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
